window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Veronica McAllister died in 2018.</p> <p>She immediately opened her eyes again in 1958, all memories of her previous life intact.</p> <p>She goes from old age, pants suits, and a cane, to poodle skirts, saddle shoes, and Buddy Holly.</p> <p>At the end of her first life, Veronica said she “wasn’t any good at life.” With the most precious of gifts - perspective and a second chance - can she succeed where she failed during her first life?</p> <p>What would you do, if you could do it all again?</p> <p><i>Includes a special bonus note read by the author.</i></p>"; 
